Package: honcho-inspector-ui
Version: 0.1.0-SNAPSHOT
Section: web
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: cloudBSD <admin@cloudbsd.org>
Depends: nodejs (>= 20), npm, adduser
Recommends: ca-certificates
Description: Honcho Inspector UI
 Angular 22 view-only dashboard for the Honcho Inspector backend.
 Provides a self-contained web UI on port 4200 with profile
 management, workspace inspection, and admin tools. Runs the Angular
 dev server (ng serve) as a node app under systemd, bound to all
 interfaces.
 .
 node_modules is NOT shipped -- the systemd unit runs `npm ci` as
 ExecStartPre on first boot so the right native binaries (esbuild,
 rollup) for the host architecture get pulled automatically. This
 keeps the deb genuinely Architecture: all (amd64, arm64, etc.)
 instead of being an amd64-only package with linux-x64 binaries
 hard-coded. First-boot cost: 30-60s of npm install.

